  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This also English name.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Good morning.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Edward Polidi-- P-O-L-I-D-I, Edward-- E-D-W-A-R-D.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm born in Sofia, Bulgaria, the year of 1935, 23rd of December, first day of the winter.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As my memoirs of stories that were said to me by my father, speak that it was extremely cold day with lot of snow.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] This produced difficulties for the transportation of my mother to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the delivery was done in my own house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this was in Sophia, [INAUDIBLE] number 55, and [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] third floor there, apartment number eight.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The-- they told me that when I was born, I was going to be a very lucky, fortunate, and [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] happy, happy person.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The story goes that I was born with these circles in my head.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was behaving after, of course, the first few hours, as a very, very happy child.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Very early in my childhood, they discerned that the things that was attracting me was the sounds, specially music sounds.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And since my mother was, in her early days, singing with the opera theater there in the choir, I had access pretty early in my life to the music of very great masters, such as Mozart, the music of Verdi, music of Rossini, Puccini, operistic music specially, and of course, some of the songs of Schubert.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Everything what was singably beautiful was on this time somewhat familiar with me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this how happened that in very early days of my life, I somehow got involved with music.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "This was happening in my third birthday when some of the, the guests brought me some-- a little toy violin and one toy, something like xylophone.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
